The paper deals with complexity classification of counting problems, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The use of holographic reductions and complex valued functions suggests a connection to computational complexity theory, which is covered by cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also deals with graph theory and symmetric functions, which are covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively. The use of dichotomy theorems suggests a connection to discrete mathematics, which is covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of counting CSP, which is covered by cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Languages).
